{
  "text": "percent was plotted against the volume of extract added to obtain a linear regression line. The slope of the regression line was compared with that of a standard Trolox solution to calculate antioxidant capacity of carrot powders, expressed as Trolox equivalent antioxidant capacity (TEAC)/g carrot powder. Among the assortment of antioxidant capacity assessment methods, only the ABTS and oxygen radical absorbance capacity assays are able to determine both lipophilic and hydrophilic antioxidant capacities of foods [CITATION_1] . We chose ABTS over oxygen radical absorbance capacity, because it has been successfully applied in the determination of tissue and serum antioxidant capacity [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , which was an aim of this investigation.",
